-- Peru March Tax Collection Rises 5.8% From Year Earlier
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2012-04-02T21:28:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/peru-march-tax-collection-rises-5-8-from-year-earlier-1-.html
Peru’s  tax collection  rose 5.8
percent to 7.53 billion soles ($2.82 billion) in March from the
same month a year earlier, the government said.  Income tax collection rose 12 percent while sales tax
gained 6 percent, said the government’s tax collection agency in
an e-mailed statement.  Imports climbed 17 percent to $3.45 billion last month, led
by machinery and vehicles, the agency said. For the first
quarter, imports rose 17 percent to $9.77 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
